FBIS4-27784 "dreas108__a94015" FBIS-EAS-94-108-A Daily Report 6 June 1994 ANNEX Japan Kono Urges Continued Dialogue With DPRK Kono Urges Continued Dialogue With DPRK OW0606020094 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 6 Jun 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW0606020094 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database Japanese BFN [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 6 June Morning Edition] [Text] Yohei Kono, president of the Liberal Democratic Party [LDP], gave a news conference in Fukuoka City on 5 June, in which he commented on how to deal with the DPRK's (North Korea) suspected development of nuclear arms. He said: "It is necessary to exert efforts to make North Korea understand correctly the appeals and demands of the international community." He stressed that priority should be given to continuing the dialogue with the DPRK.
